<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
    <id>430535</id>
    <title>htm-file in unicode doesn't import css-file in ansi</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">When a htm-file is saved in unicode format and the corresponding css is in ansi format, the css doesn't get loaded.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">If both are in ansi it works and if both are in unicode it also works.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Steps to Reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.2">1 Create htm which includes a css:</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.3">&lt;link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="style.css"&gt;</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.4">save the htm-file in unicode format.</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.5">2 Create a css file "style.css", save it in ansi format</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.6">3 Open the htm in firefox</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.7">Actual Results:</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.8">No design elements appear, the css clearly doesn't get loaded.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">Expected Results:  
The css file should load just like when its in unicode too.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
